The paper discusses the challenges of data transmission in content delivery networks (CDN) and proposes the use of edge networks as an extension to CDN networks. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. The paper also discusses the use of Mobile Edge Computing (MEC) servers to assist each other in caching and processing tasks, which falls under the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) category. The focus on Video on Demand (VoD) and multimedia content suggests that the paper may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) category. The paper proposes a probabilistic model to evaluate chunk popularities and introduces popularity-aware policies, which falls under the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) category. Finally, the paper proposes an online algorithm for scheduling collaborative caching and processing, which falls under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category.
